              "type": "paragraph",
              "content": [
                {
                  "text": "• Ensure the list of options is clearly labeled and sorted logically (e.g., alphabetically or by frequency of use). ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "type": "hardBreak"
                },
                {
                  "text": "• Use drop-downs when there are many options but not when the list is small—use ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "radio buttons",
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "text": " or ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "checklists",
                  "type": "text",
                  "marks": [
                    {
                      "type": "bold"
                    }
                  ]
                },
                {
                  "text": " for a more visible selection. ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "type": "hardBreak"
                },
                {
                  "text": "• Always display a default or placeholder option that indicates the user needs to make a selection. ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "type": "hardBreak"
                },
                {
                  "text": "• Ensure drop-downs are easy to interact with on both desktop and mobile devices. ",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "mXrjcashAb",
        "type": "dont",
        "content": {
